msgstr "[REVIEW: untranslated] Give priority to server ciphersuite order."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1127
msgid "Forces synchronization of updates to disk."
msgstr "[REVIEW: untranslated] Forces synchronization of updates to disk."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1128
msgid "The server will use the fsync() system call in several places to make sure that updates are physically written to disk. This ensures that a database cluster will recover to a consistent state after an operating system or hardware crash."
msgstr "[REVIEW: untranslated] The server will use the fsync() system call in several places to make sure that updates are physically written to disk. This ensures that a database cluster will recover to a consistent state after an operating system or hardware crash."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1139
msgid "Continues processing after a checksum failure."
msgstr "[REVIEW: untranslated] Continues processing after a checksum failure."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1140
msgid "Detection of a checksum failure normally causes PostgreSQL to report an error, aborting the current transaction. Setting ignore_checksum_failure to true causes the system to ignore the failure (but still report a warning), and continue processing. This behavior could cause crashes or other serious problems. Only has an effect if checksums are enabled."
msgstr "[REVIEW: transaction; sentence] Detection of a checksum failure normally causes PostgreSQL to report an त्रुटि, aborting the current transaction. Setting ignore_checksum_failure to true causes the system to ignore the failure (but still report a चेतावनी), and continue processing. This behavior could cause crashes or other serious problems. Only has an effect if checksums are enabled."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1154
msgid "Continues processing past damaged page headers."
msgstr "[REVIEW: untranslated] Continues processing past damaged page headers."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1155
msgid "Detection of a damaged page header normally causes PostgreSQL to report an error, aborting the current transaction. Setting \"zero_damaged_pages\" to true causes the system to instead report a warning, zero out the damaged page, and continue processing. This behavior will destroy data, namely all the rows on the damaged page."
msgstr "[REVIEW: transaction; sentence] Detection of a damaged page header normally causes PostgreSQL to report an त्रुटि, aborting the current transaction. Setting \"zero_damaged_pages\" to true causes the system to instead report a चेतावनी, zero out the damaged page, and continue processing. This behavior will destroy data, नामly all the rows on the damaged page."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1168
msgid "Continues recovery after an invalid pages failure."
msgstr "[REVIEW: recovery] Continues recovery after an अमान्य pages failure."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1169
msgid "Detection of WAL records having references to invalid pages during recovery causes PostgreSQL to raise a PANIC-level error, aborting the recovery. Setting \"ignore_invalid_pages\" to true causes the system to ignore invalid page references in WAL records (but still report a warning), and continue recovery. This behavior may cause crashes, data loss, propagate or hide corruption, or other serious problems. Only has an effect during recovery or in standby mode."
msgstr "[REVIEW: recovery, standby, WAL; sentence] Detection of WAL records having references to अमान्य pages during recovery causes PostgreSQL to raise a PANIC-level त्रुटि, aborting the recovery. Setting \"ignore_invalid_pages\" to true causes the system to ignore अमान्य page references in WAL records (but still report a चेतावनी), and continue recovery. This behavior may cause crashes, data loss, propagate or hide corruption, or other serious problems. Only has an effect during recovery or in standby mode."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1187
msgid "Writes full pages to WAL when first modified after a checkpoint."
msgstr "[REVIEW: checkpoint, WAL; untranslated] Writes full pages to WAL when first modified after a checkpoint."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1188
msgid "A page write in process during an operating system crash might be only partially written to disk.  During recovery, the row changes stored in WAL are not enough to recover.  This option writes pages when first modified after a checkpoint to WAL so full recovery is possible."
msgstr "[REVIEW: checkpoint, recovery, WAL; untranslated] A page write in process during an operating system crash might be only partially written to disk.  During recovery, the row changes stored in WAL are not enough to recover.  This option writes pages when first modified after a checkpoint to WAL so full recovery is possible."

#: utils/misc/guc_tables.c:1201
msgid "Writes full pages to WAL when first modified after a checkpoint, even for a non-critical modification."
msgstr "[REVIEW: checkpoint, WAL; untranslated] Writes full pages to WAL when first modified after a checkpoint, even for a non-critical modification."

